HEADWORD: Tampico fibre
<hw>Tam*pi"co fi"bre</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <def>A tough vegetable fiber used as a substitute
for bristles in making brushes. The piassava and the ixtle are both used
under this name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tamping</ent>⟦br⟧
